# Local CI Parity

Three tiers for day-to-day work; **full CI parity only before opening a PR**. GitHub Actions
remains the merge gate.

## When to run what

| When | Command | What |
|------|---------|------|
| While editing | Hooks (auto) | `format` + `lint-fix` + scoped typecheck on edited file |
| Agent stop | `make check-fast` + `make test-fast` | Lint + typecheck; scoped unit tests |
| Before commit | `make check` | Lint + format-check + typecheck (manual) |
| **git push** (Husky) | `make check-fast` + `make test-fast` | Fast tier â€” lint + typecheck + scoped unit tests |
| **Before opening PR** | `make ci-push` or `make ci-pr-ready` | Full CI parity locally |

Hook scripts: `.cursor/hooks/make_format_lint_fix.py`, `.cursor/hooks/typecheck.py`,
`.cursor/hooks/make_ci_on_stop.py`.

Stop-hook failures are **advisory** (do not block ending the session).

## Tier 1 â€” Fast (agent edit + stop hook)

| When | Command | What |
|------|---------|------|
| After save | Hooks | `format` + `lint-fix` + scoped `typecheck` on edited file |
| Agent stop | `make check-fast` + `make test-fast` | Lint + typecheck; unit tests for changed components only |

## Tier 2 â€” Medium (before commit; optional on push)

```bash
make check          # lint + format-check + typecheck
make test-fast      # scoped unit tests
make test-coverage-fe FE_APP=data-management-frontend  # one app's coverage loop
```

Husky `.husky/pre-push` runs **Tier 1** (`make check-fast` + `make test-fast`) â€” not full CI.
Format-check, audit, full pytest, coverage gate, and frontend production builds run in GitHub CI.

Opt-in medium pre-push: `VECINITA_MEDIUM_PRE_PUSH=1 git push` (adds format-check).

## Tier 3 â€” Full (before PR; optional on push)

```bash
make ci-push        # or: make ci-pr-ready
```

Includes: `ci-guards`, lint, format-check, typecheck, audit, full pytest, both Vitest suites,
unit coverage gate, frontend production build.

Run manually **before marking a PR ready for review**. GitHub CI runs the same checks on push.

Opt-in full parity on every push: `VECINITA_FULL_PRE_PUSH=1 git push`.

Skip pre-push entirely (emergencies only): `VECINITA_SKIP_PRE_PUSH=1 git push`.

`make ci` still includes `install` for explicit full local runs; `ci-push` skips reinstall.

## Agent must fix manually

Issues hooks cannot auto-fix: type errors, non-auto-fixable lint, test failures, CI guards, audit CVEs.

